19 SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 17-116.23 of Title 70, unless
21 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 Any person receiving benefits from the Teachers’ Retirement
23 System of Oklahoma as of June 30, 2026, who continues to receive
24
SB1144 HFLR Page 46
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

RBS No. 3869
1 bene fits on or after the effective date of this section, shall
2 receive an increase in benefits as follows:
3 1. Zero percent (0%) if the person has been retired for less
4 than eight (8) years as of June 30, 2026;
5 2. Three percent (3%) if the person has been retired for at
6 least eight (8) years but less than twenty (20) years as of June 30,
7 2026; and
8 3. Six percent (6%) if the person has been retired for twenty
9 (20) years or more as of June 30, 2026.
10 SECTION 7. Section 2 of this act shall become effective October
11 1, 2026.
12 SECTION 8. Sections 1, 3, 4, 5, and 6 of this act shall become
13 effective November 1, 2026.
